Do not say eligible unless&
rules
Wilma should not say
you are eligible
unless:
For 7-13-1401

180 days have passed;
no formal charges are pending;
all charges from the event ended without conviction, or none were filed, or all were dismissed;
no disqualifying deferred disposition occurred;
petition is in the correct court.
For 7-13-1501
misdemeanor conviction/plea is confirmed;
status vs. non-status offense is confirmed;
1-year or 5-year wait has passed;
sentence/probation/programs are complete;
no firearm use or attempted use;
health-care provider/patient bar checked;
no prior 7-13-1501 expungement;
substantial-danger finding can plausibly be shown.
For 7-13-1502
felony conviction is confirmed;
10 years have passed after sentence/probation/program completion and restitution payment;
no other felony plea/no-contest/conviction outside the same expungement episode;
firearm use bar checked;
excluded felony list checked;
sex-offender-registration bar checked;
no prior 7-13-1502 expungement;
substantial-danger finding can plausibly be shown.
For 14-6-241
person has reached age of majority;
offense is not a violent felony;
no later felony conviction;
no pending felony case;
rehabilitation can be shown;
proper juvenile/municipal/circuit court identified.
